://github.com/BafS","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BafS/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-02-05T14:54:58Z","updated_at":"2019-02-05T15:41:40Z","body":"@epdenouden Thank you for your message ! The \"terminal\" is the default gitlab web terminal.\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n[root@runner-5dda6155-project-56-concurrent-0 /]# echo $TERM;\r\nxterm\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe \"problem\" is just that it outputs the stream directly without clearing anything. It's not an interactive terminal when you run the tests but more an STDOUT stream.\r\n\r\nI simply use `--testdox --no-cover` and the xml options are\r\n\r\n```ini\r\n backupGlobals=\"false\"\r\n backupStaticAttributes=\"false\"\r\n verbose=\"true\"\r\n colors=\"true\"\r\n convertErrorsToExceptions=\"true\"\r\n convertNoticesToExceptions=\"true\"\r\n convertWarningsToExceptions=\"true\"\r\n processIsolation=\"false\"\r\n stopOnFailure=\"false\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks for your help","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/comments/460666964/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"BafS","id":588205,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODIwNQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/588205?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users