9957,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"_As a_ developer of slower integration tests\r\n_I want to_ see prettified tests results as soon as tests are completed\r\n_so that_ my workflow is both agile and Ã¦sthetic\r\n\r\n## Background ##\r\nThe [buffering testdox printer](#3417) and its friend [the spinner](#3513) are [breaking some workflows](https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/3560#issuecomment-473871720) that people used to good effect.\r\n\r\nThe example from #3560 is using Testdox to get readable results while running. The actual test order is not that important, set by configuration or implied by test collection structure. My implementation of the buffering printer breaks this specific use case.\r\n\r\n## Solution ##\r\nImplement explicit \"do not buffer result ouput\" option, along the lines of #3513:\r\n- [x] extend buffering mechanism to explicitly support always-flush\r\n- [x] add CLI flag\r\n- [x] add end-to-end tests voor `--enable-buffer` and `--disable-buffer` flag\r\n- [x] add XML-configuration option\r\n- [x] add unit test coverage for unbuffered Testdox\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/3567/reactions","total_count":7,"+1":7,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/3567/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]